<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1933-01-13T03:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1933-01-13T03:00:00-05:00" n="50" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d50">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94/5755: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in China (<persName type="from">Johnson</persName>) to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                    State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Peiping</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1933-01-13T16:00:00+08:00">January 13, 1933—4
                                p.m.</date><lb/>[Received January 13—5:42 a.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>46. Nanking’s January 10, 5 p.m., regarding Boxer protocol. Spanish
                            Minister, French Minister, Italian Minister, British Chargé d’Affaires
                            and I discussed this note, agreed that as Chinese asked nothing there
                            was nothing for us to do but to await instructions from our respective
                            Governments.</p>
                        <p>Other colleagues to be furnished informal suggestion contained in Peck’s
                            last paragraph.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Johnson</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>